juju-installer (0.2.1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Stream service-side progress live to the user's terminal. Service
    scripts now write [N/M] milestones over the existing socket (stdout)
    instead of stderr; the wrapper's new relay_progress reads each line
    and rewrites the user's rolling progress slot via show_progress, so
    the long snap-install + Canonical-K8s bootstrap phase no longer
    looks like a hang at [1/9].
  * Surface service-side ERROR: lines permanently (not overwritten by
    subsequent progress); EOF without the "1" terminator emits an
    "exited unexpectedly. Run: sudo journalctl -u <unit>@\* -e" hint.
    Unreachable socket emits a "cannot reach <unit>" hint.
  * Renumber to coherent shared sequences: K8s [1/9]..[9/9], LXD
    [1/5]..[5/5], snap-only [1/1] (visible for the first time).
    [8/9] is reused for the two cloud-register / bootstrap sub-steps
    inside do_bootstrap_k8s.
  * Service scripts redirect underlying tool chatter (snap install,
    k8s bootstrap, lxd init) to the journal via >&2 2>&1, keeping the
    socket clean for the framed protocol.
  * Tests: new mock-service helper spawns a real AF_UNIX listener with a
    readiness sentinel; 8 new wrapper-level protocol tests + 3 new
    service-level Layer-3 tests bring the suite to 69 tests.
  * Resolve shellcheck SC2015 in test_services.sh chatter-leak assertions
    (replace `A && B || C` pattern with `if A; then B; fi`).

 -- Alex Lutay <alex.lutay@canonical.com>  Wed, 13 May 2026 12:25:00 +0000

